===Etymology===
From {{bor|en|de|strafen|strafe|punish}} (a conjugated form of {{m|de|strafen}}), from phrases like "''Gott strafe England''" ("God punish England") which the British saw during the First World War.<ref>{{R:MWO}}</ref><ref>''The Handbook of Historical Sociolinguistics'' (2012, {{ISBN|140519068X}})</ref>

